### Auth-system API — manual test scratchpad
### Use with the VS Code "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client).
### Each `### name=...` block exports its response into variables you can
### reference below as {{name.response.body.$.field}}.

@host = http://localhost:4000
@email = user@example.com
@password = VeryStrongPassword123!

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Health
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
### Health check (verifies API + DB connectivity)
GET {{host}}/health


# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Register a new user
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
### Register
# After this fires, open MailHog at http://localhost:8025
# and click the verification link in the inbox.
# @name register
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "name": "Test User"
}


# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Verify email
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
### Verify email (paste token from the MailHog link)
# The mailer sends a URL like:
#   http://localhost:4000/api/auth/verify-email?token=<token>
# Copy the token value here:
@verifyToken = paste-token-from-mailhog-here

GET {{host}}/api/auth/verify-email?token={{verifyToken}}


# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. Login
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
### Login (rate limited: 5 / minute)
# Login sets an HttpOnly `refreshToken` cookie at Path=/api/auth.
# REST Client follows Set-Cookie automatically, so subsequent requests
# in this file send the cookie back for you.
# @name login
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###
# Capture access token from the login response (refresh is in the cookie)
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.accessToken}}


# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. Protected route — current user
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
### GET /api/users/me  (requires Bearer access token)
GET {{host}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 6. Refresh access token
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
### Rotate the access token (refresh cookie sent automatically; no body needed)
# @name refresh
POST {{host}}/api/auth/refresh

###
# Capture the rotated access token. The refresh cookie has been replaced.
@accessToken2 = {{refresh.response.body.accessToken}}

### Sanity check — call /me with the rotated access token
GET {{host}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken2}}


# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 6b. Logout
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
### Clears the refresh cookie + revokes the server-side token (204)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/logout

### Refresh after logout should now fail with 401
POST {{host}}/api/auth/refresh


# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 7. Forgot password / reset password
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
### Request a password reset (always returns 200 — don't leak existence)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

###
# Pull the reset token out of MailHog and paste it here:
@resetToken = c2ea0d7a3bf70063d94afd0779c5e34bc9aec763fed6466caa75a731cebe40e6
@newPassword = AnotherStrongPassword456!

### Reset password
POST {{host}}/api/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{resetToken}}",
  "password": "{{newPassword}}"
}


# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 8. Admin-only routes (requires a user with role = ADMIN)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
### List all users (ADMIN only — expect 403 with a USER token)
GET {{host}}/api/users/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Delete a user by id (ADMIN only)
DELETE {{host}}/api/users/admin/users/REPLACE_WITH_USER_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 9. Negative paths — useful to confirm the guards work
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
### Login with wrong password → 401
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "wrong-password"
}

### /me without a token → 401
GET {{host}}/api/users/me

### /me with a garbage token → 401
GET {{host}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer not-a-real-jwt

### Register the same email twice → 409
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "name": "Duplicate"
}
